Here is the cleaned up text:

OmniStudio provides a suite of services, components, and data model objects that combine to create Industry Cloud applications. Create guided interactions using data from your Salesforce org and external sources.

What Can You Do with OmniStudio?

Contain the user-interaction logic with OmniScripts.
Transfer and transform data between Salesforce and other tools with Omnistudio Data Mappers.
Bundle server-side data integration operations for efficiency and reuse with Integration Procedures.
Display data and launch actions with FlexCards.

Standard OmniStudio Content and Runtime
With the OmniStudio permission set license, standard OmniStudio content runs in standard runtime. Standard OmniStudio components built by Salesforce Industries are available.

OmniStudio Naming Conventions
Follow the naming conventions when creating an OmniStudio component.

OmniStudio sObject Descriptions
The table lists OmniStudio sObjects, their descriptions, and which objects you must grant read access to.

OmniStudio Basics
Build Service Consoles and Industry Cloud Apps with the basic building blocks of OmniStudio.

OmniScripts
An OmniScript is a business tool built on the Salesforce platform. OmniScripts allow you to craft dynamic customer interactions without code and deploy to multiple channels and devices.

OmniStudio FlexCards
Build industry-specific UI components and applications on the Salesforce platform with OmniStudio FlexCards.

Omnistudio Data Mappers
A Data Mapper enables you to read, transform, and write Salesforce data. There are four types of Data Mapper: Turbo Extract, Extract, Transform, and Load.

OmniStudio Integration Procedures
OmniStudio Integration Procedures are declarative, server-side processes that execute multiple actions in a single server call.

Formulas and Functions
The Expression Engine is an APEX-based formula builder used across multiple areas in OmniStudio.

OmniAnalytics Overview
Use OmniAnalytics to track user interactions with LWC OmniScripts and FlexCards.
title: Understanding OmniStudio
